DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270311T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270311T213000
DTSTAMP:20260714T051736Z
UID:occ-1093@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Heidi Schreck's Tony-nominated play revisiting her teenage Con
 stitution-debate speeches\, in its Atlanta premiere.\n\nHeidi Schreck put 
 herself through college giving prize-winning speeches about the Constituti
 on at American Legion halls\; her 2019 Broadway play returns to those cont
 ests\, toggling between her fifteen-year-old self and the woman she became
 . What starts as a debate exercise opens into the stories of the women in 
 her family and how the document actually treated them — funny\, personal
 \, and pointed by turns. A Tony nominee for Best Play and a Pulitzer final
 ist\, it gets its Atlanta premiere from Theatrical Outfit.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260714T051315Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
